Read-Access Geo-Redundant Storage (RA-GRS) allows read access to data in the secondary region.

This enables applications to access backup data even when the primary region is unavailable.

For example, if the primary region fails, users can still read data from the secondary region.

A real-life use case is global applications serving read-only data during outages.

Another example is analytics systems reading replicated data without impacting primary workloads.

RA-GRS improves availability and accessibility during failures.
